meta {
  name: 4.2 Vague summer prize - transformed (recovers)
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/ask/transformed-rag
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "question": "what was that summer thing they mentioned where you could win something?"
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
}

docs {
  # Beat 4 — fix it (transformed RAG, same vague question)

  Identical vague question to `4.1`, but this endpoint runs a
  **CompressingQueryTransformer** first: the model rewrites the woolly question
  into a sharp, self-contained one ("what summer photo contest / prize does the
  newsletter mention?") **before** retrieval. Better query → right chunks → the
  answer recovers.

  **Expected:** the real summer-photo gift-card answer comes back, even though the
  user's wording never changed.

  Note: this endpoint makes an **extra** LLM call (the rewrite), so it's slower —
  noticeably so on local Ollama (~2x). Don't be surprised by the latency; it's the
  cost of the rewrite, and worth calling out on stage.
}
